 (www.common-core.org). The aim of the assessment is to test how the Draft Common Frame of Reference could work when applied in different national legal systems. To this end, a number of factual situations, i.e. hypothetical cases, have been drafted by the authors and solved through the application of both national rules and rules of the DCFR. Thereby, similarities and differences in the outcome of the cases have been analysed, together with difficulties - if any - in the application of the "Principles of European Law". The Common Core assessment has been carried out as part of the "Joint Network of European Private Law" Project (CoPECL), financed by the EU Commission.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCivil lawxInternational unificationxEuropexEuropexEuropexEuropean Union countries. 0aCivil lawzEuropexInternational unification. 0aConflict of lawsxContractsxEuropean Union countries. 0aConflict of lawsxContractszEuropean Union countries. 0aContractsxEuropean Union countries. 0aContractszEuropean Union countries. 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh1 aAnatoniolli, Luisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAntoniolli, Luisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBineva, Valentina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiorentini, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiorentini, Francesca, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGómez Ligüerre, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIoriatti Ferrari, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMak, Vanessa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeier, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r